article.description: Guard Jack Gibbs scored 35 points and Davidson held off Central Florida 90-85 in the season opener for both teams Saturday night.
article.headline: Davidson holds off Central Florida 90-85
article.story: DAVIDSON, N.C. -- Guard Jack Gibbs scored 35 points and Davidson held off Central Florida 90-85 in the season opener for both teams Saturday night. Last year, the 6-foot Gibbs scored more than 30 twice, becoming the first Davidson player with multiple 30-point games since Stephen Curry in 2008-09. Gibbs scored a career-high 37 shooting 15 of 17 last season. He wasn't as efficient Saturday night though, shooting 12 for 23 from the field and 9 for 10 from the free-throw line. The Wildcats used a 16-5 run to start the second half and took a 61-60 lead. Gibbs then proceeded to make two free throws, a layup, a 3-pointer and another layup to make the score 69-63 and Central Florida never led again. Brian Sullivan and Jordan Barham each had 15 points for the Wildcats. Adonys Henriquez scored 18 points for Central Florida.
